rComments: My Absolute Favourite Professor at UTM. I honestly wish he thought more classes! So kind and very inspirational. He is very caring, remembers his students and encourages everyone to do their best, making him such an amazing professor. His tests are extremely easy and he gives you time in advance to prepare. The Assignments are amazing. Just Perfect

Zaheer is genuinely a good professor, he cares about the success of his students. He gives out the test questions for the midterms, and the 2 assignments are straight forward and easy to do well on. The lectures can be very long and confusing but reading the textbook and looking over your lecture notes helped a lot for the test and assignments.
Weird teaching style but sometimes an easy marker. He also gives out the test questions ahead of time

Loved this class, made a mandatory credit simple. We had two essays and two tests, I usually do alright on essays (mid-high 70s) I got 90s in this course I was shook. But it's because the professor explains things clearly and tells you exactly what to expect on the test so you gucci. If I did good, you'll do good trust me, take it.
Awesome Professor! His method of teaching makes everything very simple and easy to follow. Would love to be in another class with Professor Baber again.

My favorite professor at UTM! Going to class is always a joy. The tests are fair, the content is interesting and topical. Such a fantastic lecturer. I can't recommend his courses enough. Such a wonderful person as well. Makes an effort to get to know students, and wants everyone to succeed. Second class I have taken with Professor Baber!

He is funny and loves his students. If you come to lectures you wont have a hard time passing his classes with an A. He's not one of those profs who makes you kill yourself to get good marks, he wants you to succeed. If you're looking for a courses to do well in, take a course with Baber. He's also hilarious and very kind! 10/10 recommend

Zaheer is a very good lecturer, however lectures are not mandatory. He is very intelligent and loves to teach and does his best to help students understand. He gives out the essay questions before the test (2 tests), and the research paper was fair, and graded fair also. I recommend taking this class.

I attended only 4 lectures and passed the class with an A, it is not necessary to attend lectures. He gives out all of the test questions ahead of time, they are researchable and he e-mails the lecture slides so you can check them out. There was only 2 tests and one essay, they were all graded fairly.
Prof Baber gives out the test questions beforehand. (Like give out 7 and 3 will be on the test) Reading and searching for relevant materials online, prepare them and a good grade is guaranteed.

AMAZING professor!!! Very kind, helpful and passionate about what he teaches! His obsession with Marx got me obsessed to Marx's work as well! Important to attend lectures as he tests on material from mainly lectures and provides good examples to understand concepts very well! Loved the course, definitely taking more courses with him!

Professor Baber made what appeared to be a very boring class a little more fun and interesting. Although his accent was sort of hard to understand, I thought he was a great teacher. Very helpful. Textbook wasn't really necessary, but I bought it anyway. His assignments and tests were fair, and I ended up with an 80 something.
Very nice professor but I found he was difficult to understand in lecture which made it hard to pay attention
AMAAZING professor, although his obsession with Marx was pretty funny. Loved him.

awesome prof, clear and tests/exam were easy. doesn't use textbook much, more so used google on my own to study and did well. he's funny and interesting and really wants students to do well in class/life.
Baber is an excellent prof, he truly wants his students to succeed. Loves sociology. Overall great prof and a great person!

amazing prof. his lectures are clear and forward. very funny and keeps you interested. always willing to help and his tests are straight forward from lectures. go to his lectures and take notes, study them and you will ace the tests.

Professor Baber is great. I'd say he's one of the best Sociology profs at utm - passionate about the discipline, cares about students, obviously enjoys teaching, and has a clear and straightforward lecturing style.
He is a great professor! Very interesting lectures, and really kind as well.
BEST proff i have had. hes just amazing and so understanding. The 3 tests very easy and very broad.

Amazing Professor! Enjoyed his class. Good power point notes. Had 3 tests- all were easy. Material straight from the lecture. Very helpful. Will look over work/re-mark. Wish he taught more sociology courses.
boring material, boring book chosen, couldnt understand what he was saying half the time, good use of powerpoint, tests were very fair.
I LOVED HIM. he is such a great prof. I would definately want to have him again. HES THE BEST!!

I had him for both 232 & 354 and he really was great in the 354. All his examples are current and relavent and he made me think. No exams and he usually gives essay questions out. Quick wit and though sometimes I wouldnt get the jokes it'd be because he was poking fun at himself. Overall really great - wish he taught more courses
Course seemed difficult at first, but once u attend classes, you'll see that he is approchable and his tests are very easy. NO Final Exam. A good course to take.

Lots of reading, but if you like the material you would enjoy the course.  Tests are easy like mac and cheese & he's very fair.  He's flexible - he changed the syllabus for us!  There was one open book test which we love him for.  NO ESSAYS!!! Baber, you rock my globally manufactured socks.
